sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Validating Webhook<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as kuberay-operator<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>Multiple Ports
    participant Workers as Ray Workers<br/>Autoscaling
    participant GCS as Ray GCS<br/>6379/TCP
    participant Dashboard as Ray Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant Serve as Ray Serve<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Client as External Client<br/>HTTPS via Route

    Note over User,Operator: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayCluster<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate RayCluster<br/>mTLS (K8s cert)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Result
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch Event<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount, Service, Pods<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Registry: Pull Ray Image<br/>TLS 1.2+ (Pull Secret)
    Registry-->>K8sAPI: Image Layers
    K8sAPI->>HeadPod: Start Ray Head
    K8sAPI->>Workers: Start Ray Workers
    HeadPod->>GCS: Initialize GCS<br/>6379/TCP (Optional Password)
    Workers->>GCS: Register with GCS<br/>6379/TCP

    Note over User,Dashboard: Flow 2: Ray Job Submission (RayJob)
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayJob<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch Event
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Note over Operator,HeadPod: (RayCluster creation steps...)
    Operator->>Dashboard: Submit Job<br/>8265/TCP HTTP (No Auth)
    Dashboard->>GCS: Schedule Job<br/>6379/TCP
    GCS->>Workers: Distribute Tasks
    Workers->>Dashboard: Report Status
    Dashboard-->>Operator: Job Complete
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update RayJob Status

    Note over Client,Serve: Flow 3: Model Serving (RayService)
    Client->>K8sAPI: HTTPS Request via Route<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.2+ (Optional API Key)
    K8sAPI->>Serve: Forward to Ray Serve<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    Serve->>HeadPod: Ray Client Connection<br/>10001/TCP
    HeadPod->>Workers: Distribute Inference<br/>Internal TCP
    Workers-->>Serve: Inference Result
    Serve-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Operator,Dashboard: Flow 4: Monitoring
    Operator->>Operator: Expose Metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    HeadPod->>HeadPod: Expose Metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    Note right of Operator: Prometheus scrapes<br/>operator & cluster metrics
